{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i50.tinypic.com/2j7b20.'}
{'text': 'What about the heroin epidemic that has hit this country in the last 10 years? How many lives have been ruined due to heroin?'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i10.tinypic.com/1f0nqg. So there you have it. Did you make it this far?'}
{'text': 'What if people are willing to pay for a product that helps them get high and lose their inhibitions? Would it really be wrong to charge them for that service?'}
{'text': "[#][IMG]http://i29.tinypic.com/2r1b3l. It's not just recreational drug users that need to be involved in the debate."}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i1.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/000/957/571/g. http://i1.'}
{'text': '[#] [/#] Drug legalization cannot be a one step solution to the drug problem.'}
{'text': 'If it\'s not a "high then it\'s not worth it for you, and if it\'s not worth it for you then it\'s not worth it for anyone.'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i4.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/000/950/313/f.'}
{'text': 'I think that people would probably be willing to pay for something that would help them achieve the highest state of mind possible.'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i46.tinypic.com/2p4bkx.'}
{'text': 'Did we really need prohibition of alcohol or tobacco? Why do we care about drugs when they are used far less frequently than alcohol or tobacco?'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i22.tinypic.com/2b65v3.'}
{'text': 'The fact that legalizing drugs will make it easier to get them is not a reason to legalize them. In fact, the opposite is quite likely to happen.'}
{'text': 'If we legalize harmful substances, there is no reason to think that they will be used more than their present status indicates.'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2006/03/19/drug-legalization-stric_n_705085.'}
{'text': 'How many people do you think would be willing to step up to the plate and deal with their own drug problems, if they had the option?'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i18.tinypic.com/2qdp6r.'}
{'text': "It wouldn't be such a bad idea to legalize marijuana for those who are suffering from medical conditions that may be alleviated by the use of marijuana."}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i32.tinypic.com/2r5ooq.'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://ii.ytimg.com/vi/hImA0Lk6UIo/maxresdefault.'}
{'text': 'This is an issue which has existed for a long time, and hopefully, as society grows, we will find a way to cope with it.'}
{'text': 'Too many people have no idea that drugs have negative side effects.'}
{'text': "With legalization, we'll see several kinds of 'legalized' drugs. Some drugs will be legal, while others will not be."}
{'text': 'If we are serious about keeping drugs out of the hands of young people, we need to do more to teach people how to treat their addictions, and we need to come up with a solution to...'}

{'text': 'The important thing is to remove the last vestiges of the institutionalized stigma associated with drugs. To do this, we need to decriminalize the possession of drugs that are deemed illegal.'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i3.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/000/948/525/l. http://i3.'}
{'text': '[#][IMG](http://i2.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/original/000/124/7a/aa.jpg?'}
{'text': 'If you legalize drugs, do you think it will make it easier to get them legally?'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i52.tinypic.com/2b6wt9. \xa0\xa0 There are some very strong arguments against legalizing drugs.'}
{'text': 'We should not legalize drugs because we think it will make them less harmful, but because we think it will make drug abuse less prevalent.'}
{'text': "[#][IMG]http://i28.tinypic.com/2o0q0o. This is also called a liberal drug policy, and I'd agree with that."}
{'text': "[#][IMG]http://i32.tinypic.com/2g2kaw. Let's keep it in mind for future discussion."}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i3.kym-cdn.com/assets.centralparknyc.org/images/original/000/894/630/e.'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i1.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/000/925/635/f.'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i35.tinypic.com/2g9b74.'}

{'text': 'People have different ideas about which drugs should be legalized or not, but we all agree that it would be beneficial to treat drug abuse and mental illness in parallel, rather than having one set of laws for...'}
{'text': '[#][IMG]http://i42.tinypic.com/1y0b2s.'}
{'text': "Why do we punish people who don't even take drugs? What would be the point in doing that? The whole point of punishment is to deter people from doing certain things."}
{'text': 'The current system is far too harsh and inefficient, and has proven itself to be highly ineffective at stopping people from using drugs.'}
